   "source": [
    "#convert into right data types\n",
    "str(data)\n",
    "\n",
    "data$Time <- gsub('\\\\.',':',data$Time)\n",
    "data$Date <- gsub('/','-',data$Date)\n",
    "\n",
    "data$DateTime <- as.POSIXct(as.character(paste(data$Date, data$Time)), format=\"%d-%m-%Y %H:%M:%S\")\n",
    "\n",
    "data <- subset( data, select = -c(Date, Time) )\n",
    "\n",
    "data[1:6] <- lapply(data[1:6], as.numeric)"
   ]

   "source": [
    "Model:\n",
    "na.kalman and does Kalman smoothing on the state-space form of an ARIMA model\n",
    "\n",
    "Works on univariate data\n",
    "\n",
    "Dealing with missing observations by means of the Kalman filter is sometimes interpreted as extrapolation of the series; when the Kalman smoother is used, missing observations are said to be filled in by interpolation in the observed series.\n",
    "\n",
    "For Time series with strong seasonality, it performs best than mean, random sample or locf."
   ]
